==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sinigrin
<hw>Sin"i*grin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From NL.
<ets>Sinapis nigra</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A glucoside
found in the seeds of black mustard (<spn>Brassica nigra</spn>, formerly
<spn>Sinapis nigra</spn>) It resembles sinalbin, and consists of a
potassium salt of myronic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

